overview: The user's intent was to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  adding a database for storing responses and an admin dashboard for data
  access, as outlined in a Statement of Work. The approach involved a
  comprehensive evaluation of the existing codebase to identify missing
  functionalities. Key decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma
  for database management, implementing a simple password-based authentication
  system for the admin dashboard, and combining demographic data requirements
  from the SOW with existing form fields. The outcome is a plan and initial
  implementation steps for updating the application to include a
   database model, API endpoints for data submission and
  retrieval (including CSV export), and a basic admin interface for client
  access.
